author: Patrick Unson
comment: I enjoy reading what others have to say about the places they check-in to. Be it positive or negative, curiosity can sometimes make you want to check out the place anyway! The "taste" feature is useful for more personal recommendations. I started using this app enjoying earning points and monitoring the leaderboard with my friends, but it became more exciting to share tips, help others, and know how much they appreciate the help you give. Adding "tags" made photo uploads slightly more interesting.  But lately, I don't get that much interaction so I don't know how to measure the impact of my reviews and photo uploads. And I've been getting some followers with mischievous profile descriptions. I hope this can be looked into.

author: Fern H
comment: Yikes, this app takes up 1.7GB of my internal storage!  My second-biggest app, Facebook (a notorious storage hog), uses just under 500MB.  What the heck?  The only positive thing about Foursquare, where storage is concerned, is that it's able to be moved to my formatted-as-internal SD card - thank goodness for that, at least!  But it would be nice if it could default to hogging that memory without me having to move it manually, please.  Better yet, take up less room!  Is that possible?

author: Manil Chowdhury
comment: Battery usage is higher if Settings > Location Settings > Location Services is checked.  You don't need that checked to find places near you when the app is displaying on screen. It's used for the app to check location when it's not displaying, so that it can recommend places.
